page.title: 02Population in West Enfield
page.content: Most of the people surveyed were born in the British Isles but a large minority were born in Cyprus.The majority of people had moved two or three times before settling here and some had made several moves.In many cases people born in the U.K had also lived in other countries. The majority chose to live in this area because it is pleasant,leafy suburb with good schools,attractive houses and large areas of open space.It is convenient to both town and country with excellent bus,train and underground links with London.Many people already had friends or family in the area. The population is mobile with the majority having lived here for ten years or less but many expect to remain in the area for at least ten years and some plan to retire here.
